Clasificación binaria¶

En este documento se entrenan y se validan tres modelos de red neuronal para los tres inputs en los que se puede dividir nuestro dataset preprocesado. En concreto, emplearemos redes neuronales de arquitectura recurrente (RNN), redes neuronales de arquitectura totalmente conectada (fully conected), y redes neuronales de arquitectura convolucional unidimensional (CNN 1D). Estos tres tipos de red neuronal son los m√°s habituales dentro de la literatura y los m√°s adecuados dada la estructura unidimensional tan particular de nuestro dataset final.

Para cada uno de los tres tipos de red neuronal se elaborar√°n tres modelos (en total, nueve modelos). Uno primero con inputs de entrada de la visi√≥n global de las curvas de luz (2001 √ó 15757), uno segundo con la visi√≥n local (201 √ó 15757), y uno tercero con ambos inputs de entrada concatenados en un √∫nico modelo final.

En este caso, nuestra variable dependiente ser√° binaria (curva de luz con exoplaneta / curva de luz sin exoplaneta), si bien tambi√©n se podr√≠an adaptar los algoritmos a una clasificaci√≥n multiclase (PC: candidato a planeta / AFP: falso positivo astron√≥mico / NTP: fen√≥meno no transitable). He hecho pruebas y los resultados no son tan positivos como con los de este documento.

Para la construcci√≥n de los modelos se emplean las bibliotecas de Keras y Tensorflow, dos paquetes para la construcci√≥n secuencial de redes neuronales de todo tipo.

# Procedemos a realizar un downsampling para equilibrar las clases. Dispondremos en torno a 3500 curvas de luz para cada una de las clases.

global_complete_1 = global_complete[global_complete['av_training_set'] == 1]
global_complete = pd.concat([global_complete_0, global_complete_1])

local_complete_1 = local_complete[local_complete['av_training_set'] == 1]
local_complete = pd.concat([local_complete_0, local_complete_1])

Red neuronal de arquitectura recurrente (RNN)¶

Visión global¶

La estructura de los modelos es siempre la misma. En primer lugar se genera el modelo por capas, como si fuera un pastel. En este caso, en primer lugar la capa con las dimensiones del input (2001,), en segundo lugar las capas recurrentes de arquitectura LSTM, una capa de Dropout intermedia para tratar de reducir el posible sobreajuste, y una √∫ltima capa densa con activaci√≥n sigmoide que nos devolver√° las probabilidades para cada dato de entrada.

En la mayor√≠a de casos, el proceso para mejorar la performance del modelo consiste en ir probando distintas capas con distintos par√°metros hasta dar con una combinaci√≥n satisfactoria. Este proceso requiere de una gran capacidad de procesamiento con tarjetas gr√°ficas de bastante nivel. Yo he tratado de tunear cada modelo con las limitaciones del Mac, pero estoy segur√≠simo de que con un ordenador superior se podr√≠an mejorar a√∫n m√°s los resultados.

In [ ]:
from keras.models import Sequential, Model
from keras.layers import Conv1D, MaxPool1D, Dense, Dropout, Flatten, \
BatchNormalization, Input, Concatenate, Activation, InputLayer, CuDNNLSTM, LSTM, Bidirectional

model = Sequential()
model.add(Input(shape=x_train.shape[1:]))
model.add(LSTM(units=16, return_sequences=True))
model.add(LSTM(units=32, return_sequences=True))
model.add(LSTM(units=64))
model.add(Dropout(0.25))
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))

Tras la creaci√≥n del modelo, generamos una funci√≥n que nos permite generar batchs o paquetes de datos para optimizar el proceso de entrenamiento. En este caso, a parte de generar estos paquetes, la funci√≥n aprovecha para rotar aleatoriamente cada dato en el tiempo, de manera que cada paquete contenga ejemplos de cada clase y no se favorezca a ninguna durante el proceso de entrenamiento.

In [ ]:
def batch_generator(x_train, y_train, batch_size=64):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2
    x_batch = np.empty((batch_size, x_train.shape[1], x_train.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch = np.empty((batch_size, y_train.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    
    yes_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 1.)[0]
    non_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 0.)[0]
    
    while True:
        np.random.shuffle(yes_idx)
        np.random.shuffle(non_idx)
    
        x_batch[:half_batch] = x_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch[half_batch:] = x_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch[:half_batch] = y_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch[half_batch:] = y_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
    
        for i in range(batch_size):
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch.shape[1])
            x_batch[i] = np.roll(x_batch[i], sz, axis = 0)
     
        yield x_batch, y_batch

A continuaci√≥n a√±adimos una nueva dimensi√≥n a los dataframes y, que son los que contienen las etiquetas de cada clase.

y_test = y_test[:, np.newaxis]
y_val = y_val[:, np.newaxis]

Ya por √∫ltimo compilamos y ajustamos el modelo a nuestros datos de validaci√≥n. Ajustaremos los epochs o iteraciones de cada modelo entre las 50 y las 100. Si pusieramos m√°s, los modelos seguramente mejorar√≠an, pero tardar√≠an demasiado en ejecutarse.

                           validation_data=(x_val, y_val), 
                           verbose=1, epochs=20,
                           steps_per_epoch=x_train.shape[1]//64)

fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_true, y_hat)
plt.plot(thresholds, 1.-fpr)
plt.plot(thresholds, tpr)
plt.show()
crossover_index = np.min(np.where(1.-fpr <= tpr))
crossover_cutoff = thresholds[crossover_index]
crossover_specificity = 1.-fpr[crossover_index]
print("Crossover al {0:.2f} con especificidad {1:.2f}".format(crossover_cutoff, crossover_specificity))

model = Sequential()
model.add(Input(shape=x_train_local.shape[1:]))
model.add(LSTM(units=16, return_sequences=True))
model.add(LSTM(units=32, return_sequences=True))
model.add(LSTM(units=64))
model.add(Dropout(0.25))
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
In [ ]:
def batch_generator(x_train_local, y_train_local, batch_size=64):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2
    x_batch = np.empty((batch_size, x_train_local.shape[1], x_train_local.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch = np.empty((batch_size, y_train_local.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    
    yes_idx = np.where(y_train_local[:,0] == 1.)[0]
    non_idx = np.where(y_train_local[:,0] == 0.)[0]
    
    while True:
        np.random.shuffle(yes_idx)
        np.random.shuffle(non_idx)
    
        x_batch[:half_batch] = x_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch[half_batch:] = x_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch[:half_batch] = y_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch[half_batch:] = y_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
    
        for i in range(batch_size):
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch.shape[1])
            x_batch[i] = np.roll(x_batch[i], sz, axis = 0)
     
        yield x_batch, y_batch

fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_true, y_hat)
plt.plot(thresholds, 1.-fpr)
plt.plot(thresholds, tpr)
plt.show()
crossover_index = np.min(np.where(1.-fpr <= tpr))
crossover_cutoff = thresholds[crossover_index]
crossover_specificity = 1.-fpr[crossover_index]
print("Crossover al {0:.2f} con especificidad {1:.2f}".format(crossover_cutoff, crossover_specificity))

from keras.models import Sequential, Model
from keras.layers import Conv1D, MaxPool1D, Dense, Dropout, Flatten, \
BatchNormalization, Input, concatenate, Activation
from keras.optimizers import Adam

# Definimos la entrada para cada modelo
input_model1 = Input(shape=x_train.shape[1:])
input_model2 = Input(shape=x_train_local.shape[1:])

# Modelo 1
x1 = LSTM(units=16, return_sequences=True)(input_model1)
x1 = LSTM(units=32, return_sequences=True)(x1)
x1 = LSTM(units=64)(x1)

# Modelo 2
x2 = LSTM(units=16, return_sequences=True)(input_model2)
x2 = LSTM(units=32, return_sequences=True)(x2)
x2 = LSTM(units=64)(x2)

# Concatenamos las salidas de ambos modelos
merged = concatenate([x1, x2])

# Definimos las capas fully-connected
x = Dropout(0.25)(merged)
final_output = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

# Creamos el modelo final
final_model = Model(inputs=[input_model1, input_model2], outputs=final_output)
In [ ]:
def batch_generator(x_train, x_train_local, y_train, y_train_local, batch_size=64):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2
    x_batch = np.empty((batch_size, x_train.shape[1], x_train.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    x_batch_local = np.empty((batch_size, x_train_local.shape[1], x_train_local.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch = np.empty((batch_size, y_train.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch_local = np.empty((batch_size, y_train_local.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    
    yes_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 1.)[0]
    non_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 0.)[0]
    
    while True:
        np.random.shuffle(yes_idx)
        np.random.shuffle(non_idx)
    
        x_batch[:half_batch] = x_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch_local[:half_batch] = x_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch[half_batch:] = x_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        x_batch_local[half_batch:] = x_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch[:half_batch] = y_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch_local[:half_batch] = y_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch[half_batch:] = y_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch_local[half_batch:] = y_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
    
        for i in range(batch_size):
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch.shape[1])
            x_batch[i] = np.roll(x_batch[i], sz, axis = 0)
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch_local.shape[1])
            x_batch_local[i] = np.roll(x_batch_local[i], sz, axis = 0)
     
        yield ([x_batch, x_batch_local], y_batch)

In [ ]:
def batch_generator(x_train, y_train, batch_size=62):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2
    x_batch = np.empty((batch_size, x_train.shape[1], x_train.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch = np.empty((batch_size, y_train.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    
    yes_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 1.)[0]
    non_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 0.)[0]
    
    while True:
        np.random.shuffle(yes_idx)
        np.random.shuffle(non_idx)
    
        x_batch[:half_batch] = x_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch[half_batch:] = x_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch[:half_batch] = y_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch[half_batch:] = y_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
    
        for i in range(batch_size):
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch.shape[1])
            x_batch[i] = np.roll(x_batch[i], sz, axis = 0)
     
        yield x_batch, y_batch

In [ ]:
y_true = (y_test[:, 0] + 0.5).astype("int")
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_true, y_hat)
plt.plot(thresholds, 1.-fpr)
plt.plot(thresholds, tpr)
plt.show()
crossover_index = np.min(np.where(1.-fpr <= tpr))
crossover_cutoff = thresholds[crossover_index]
crossover_specificity = 1.-fpr[crossover_index]
print("Crossover al {0:.2f} con especificidad {1:.2f}".format(crossover_cutoff, crossover_specificity))

Crossover at 0.42 with specificity 0.90

In [ ]:
def batch_generator(x_train_local, y_train_local, batch_size=64):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2
    x_batch = np.empty((batch_size, x_train_local.shape[1], x_train_local.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch = np.empty((batch_size, y_train_local.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    
    yes_idx = np.where(y_train_local[:,0] == 1.)[0]
    non_idx = np.where(y_train_local[:,0] == 0.)[0]
    
    while True:
        np.random.shuffle(yes_idx)
        np.random.shuffle(non_idx)
    
        x_batch[:half_batch] = x_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch[half_batch:] = x_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch[:half_batch] = y_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch[half_batch:] = y_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
    
        for i in range(batch_size):
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch.shape[1])
            x_batch[i] = np.roll(x_batch[i], sz, axis = 0)
     
        yield x_batch, y_batch

print("Crossover al {0:.2f} con especificidad {1:.2f}".format(crossover_cutoff, crossover_specificity))

from keras.models import Sequential, Model
from keras.layers import Conv1D, MaxPool1D, Dense, Dropout, Flatten, \
BatchNormalization, Input, concatenate, Activation
from keras.optimizers import Adam

# Definimos la entrada para cada modelo
input_model1 = Input(shape=x_train.shape[1:])
input_model2 = Input(shape=x_train_local.shape[1:])

# Modelo 1
x1 = Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(input_model1)
x1 = Flatten()(x1)

# Modelo 2
x2 = Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(input_model2)
x2 = Flatten()(x2)

# Concatenamos las salidas de ambos modelos despu√©s de sus capas Flatten
merged = concatenate([x1, x2])

# Definimos las capas fully-connected
x = Dense(256, activation='relu')(merged)
x = Dense(256, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dropout(0.15)(x)
x = Dense(256, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dense(256, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dropout(0.15)(x)
x = Dense(256, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dense(256, activation='relu')(x)
final_output = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

# Creamos el modelo final
final_model = Model(inputs=[input_model1, input_model2], outputs=final_output)
In [ ]:
def batch_generator(x_train, x_train_local, y_train, y_train_local, batch_size=64):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2
    x_batch = np.empty((batch_size, x_train.shape[1], x_train.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    x_batch_local = np.empty((batch_size, x_train_local.shape[1], x_train_local.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch = np.empty((batch_size, y_train.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch_local = np.empty((batch_size, y_train_local.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    
    yes_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 1.)[0]
    non_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 0.)[0]
    
    while True:
        np.random.shuffle(yes_idx)
        np.random.shuffle(non_idx)
    
        x_batch[:half_batch] = x_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch_local[:half_batch] = x_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch[half_batch:] = x_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        x_batch_local[half_batch:] = x_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch[:half_batch] = y_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch_local[:half_batch] = y_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch[half_batch:] = y_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch_local[half_batch:] = y_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
    
        for i in range(batch_size):
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch.shape[1])
            x_batch[i] = np.roll(x_batch[i], sz, axis = 0)
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch_local.shape[1])
            x_batch_local[i] = np.roll(x_batch_local[i], sz, axis = 0)
     
        yield ([x_batch, x_batch_local], y_batch)

fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_true, y_hat)
plt.plot(thresholds, 1.-fpr)
plt.plot(thresholds, tpr)

crossover_index = np.min(np.where(1.-fpr <= tpr))
crossover_cutoff = thresholds[crossover_index]
crossover_specificity = 1.-fpr[crossover_index]
print("Crossover al {0:.2f} con especificidad {1:.2f}".format(crossover_cutoff, crossover_specificity))

model = Sequential()

model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=5, strides=2))
model.add(Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))
model.add(Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=5, strides=2))
model.add(Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))
model.add(Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))

model.add(Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))
model.add(Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=5, strides=2))
model.add(Conv1D(filters=256, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))

model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=5, strides=2))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dropout(0.15))
model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
In [ ]:
def batch_generator(x_train, y_train, batch_size=64):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2
    x_batch = np.empty((batch_size, x_train.shape[1], x_train.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch = np.empty((batch_size, y_train.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    
    yes_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 1.)[0]
    non_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 0.)[0]
    
    while True:
        np.random.shuffle(yes_idx)
        np.random.shuffle(non_idx)
    
        x_batch[:half_batch] = x_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch[half_batch:] = x_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch[:half_batch] = y_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch[half_batch:] = y_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
    
        for i in range(batch_size):
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch.shape[1])
            x_batch[i] = np.roll(x_batch[i], sz, axis = 0)
     
        yield x_batch, y_batch

In [ ]:
y_true = (y_test[:, 0] + 0.5).astype("int")
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_true, y_hat)
plt.plot(thresholds, 1.-fpr)
plt.plot(thresholds, tpr)
plt.show()
crossover_index = np.min(np.where(1.-fpr <= tpr))
crossover_cutoff = thresholds[crossover_index]
crossover_specificity = 1.-fpr[crossover_index]
print("Crossover al {0:.2f} con especificidad {1:.2f}".format(crossover_cutoff, crossover_specificity))

Crossover al 0.39 con especificidad 0.94

from keras.models import Sequential, Model
from keras.layers import Conv1D, MaxPool1D, Dense, Dropout, Flatten, \
BatchNormalization, Input, concatenate, Activation
from keras.optimizers import Adam

model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv1D(filters=16, kernel_size=5, activation='relu', input_shape=x_train_local.shape[1:]))
model.add(Conv1D(filters=16, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=7, strides=2))
model.add(Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))
model.add(Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, activation='relu'))
model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=7, strides=2))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dropout(0.25))

In [ ]:
def batch_generator(x_train_local, y_train_local, batch_size=64):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2
    x_batch = np.empty((batch_size, x_train_local.shape[1], x_train_local.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch = np.empty((batch_size, y_train_local.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    
    yes_idx = np.where(y_train_local[:,0] == 1.)[0]
    non_idx = np.where(y_train_local[:,0] == 0.)[0]
    
    while True:
        np.random.shuffle(yes_idx)
        np.random.shuffle(non_idx)
    
        x_batch[:half_batch] = x_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch[half_batch:] = x_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch[:half_batch] = y_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch[half_batch:] = y_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
    
        for i in range(batch_size):
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch.shape[1])
            x_batch[i] = np.roll(x_batch[i], sz, axis = 0)
     
        yield x_batch, y_batch

Visión combinada¶

In [ ]:
from keras.models import Sequential, Model
from keras.layers import Conv1D, MaxPool1D, Dense, Dropout, Flatten, \
BatchNormalization, Input, concatenate, Activation
from keras.optimizers import Adam

# Definimos la entrada para cada modelo
input_model1 = Input(shape=x_train.shape[1:])
input_model2 = Input(shape=x_train_local.shape[1:])

# Modelo 1
x1 = Conv1D(filters=16, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(input_model1)
x1 = Conv1D(filters=16, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x1)
x1 = MaxPool1D(pool_size=5, strides=2)(x1)
x1 = Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x1)
x1 = Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x1)
x1 = MaxPool1D(pool_size=5, strides=2)(x1)
x1 = Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x1)
x1 = Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x1)
x1 = MaxPool1D(pool_size=5, strides=2)(x1)
x1 = Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x1)
x1 = Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x1)
x1 = MaxPool1D(pool_size=5, strides=2)(x1)
x1 = Conv1D(filters=256, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x1)
x1 = Conv1D(filters=256, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x1)
x1 = MaxPool1D(pool_size=5, strides=2)(x1)
x1 = Flatten()(x1)

# Modelo 2
x2 = Conv1D(filters=16, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(input_model2)
x2 = Conv1D(filters=16, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x2)
x2 = MaxPool1D(pool_size=7, strides=2)(x2)
x2 = Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x2)
x2 = Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=5, activation='relu')(x2)
x2 = MaxPool1D(pool_size=7, strides=2)(x2)
x2 = Flatten()(x2)

# Concatenamos las salidas de ambos modelos despu√©s de sus capas Flatten
merged = concatenate([x1, x2])

# Definimos las capas fully-connected
x = Dropout(0.15)(merged)
x = Dense(512, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dense(512, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dense(512, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dense(512, activation='relu')(x)
final_output = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

# Creamos el modelo final
final_model = Model(inputs=[input_model1, input_model2], outputs=final_output)

In [ ]:
def batch_generator(x_train, x_train_local, y_train, y_train_local, batch_size=64):
    half_batch = batch_size // 2
    x_batch = np.empty((batch_size, x_train.shape[1], x_train.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    x_batch_local = np.empty((batch_size, x_train_local.shape[1], x_train_local.shape[2]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch = np.empty((batch_size, y_train.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    y_batch_local = np.empty((batch_size, y_train_local.shape[1]), dtype='float32')
    
    yes_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 1.)[0]
    non_idx = np.where(y_train[:,0] == 0.)[0]
    
    while True:
        np.random.shuffle(yes_idx)
        np.random.shuffle(non_idx)
    
        x_batch[:half_batch] = x_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch_local[:half_batch] = x_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        x_batch[half_batch:] = x_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        x_batch_local[half_batch:] = x_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch[:half_batch] = y_train[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch_local[:half_batch] = y_train_local[yes_idx[:half_batch]]
        y_batch[half_batch:] = y_train[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
        y_batch_local[half_batch:] = y_train_local[non_idx[half_batch:batch_size]]
    
        for i in range(batch_size):
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch.shape[1])
            x_batch[i] = np.roll(x_batch[i], sz, axis = 0)
            sz = np.random.randint(x_batch_local.shape[1])
            x_batch_local[i] = np.roll(x_batch_local[i], sz, axis = 0)
     
        yield ([x_batch, x_batch_local], y_batch)

In [ ]:
y_true = (y_test[:, 0] + 0.5).astype("int")
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_true, y_hat)
plt.plot(thresholds, 1.-fpr)
plt.plot(thresholds, tpr)
plt.show()
crossover_index = np.min(np.where(1.-fpr <= tpr))
crossover_cutoff = thresholds[crossover_index]
crossover_specificity = 1.-fpr[crossover_index]
print("Crossover al {0:.2f} con especificidad {1:.2f}".format(crossover_cutoff, crossover_specificity))

Crossover al 0.75 con especificidad 0.93
